# Build-context excludes shared by every app image (apps/api, apps/web, apps/operator).
# Goal: keep contexts small and deterministic — dependencies and build outputs are
# (re)generated INSIDE the image, never shipped in from the host.

# --- Dependencies (reinstalled in-image via pnpm --frozen-lockfile) ---
**/node_modules

# --- Build outputs (rebuilt in-image via turbo) ---
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/out
**/build
**/next-env.d.ts
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# --- VCS / CI (not needed to build the apps) ---
.git
.gitattributes
.gitignore
.github

# --- Env & secrets (NEVER send secrets into a build context) ---
**/.env
**/.env.*

# --- Docker / compose (read by the builder directly, not needed inside the context) ---
Dockerfile
**/Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose.yml
compose.yaml
compose.yml

# --- Documentation, infra & deployment manifests (out of scope for app builds) ---
docs
infra
deploy
README.md
CLAUDE.md
*.md

# --- Logs / test / coverage artifacts ---
**/*.log
**/coverage
**/.nyc_output
**/playwright-report
**/test-results

# --- Editor / OS cruft ---
.vscode
.idea
**/*.swp
**/.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
